  "prompt": "What does fondant taste like? How is it made?",
  "response": "Fondant is a type of edible icing used to decorate cakes and pastries. Here's a breakdown of its taste and preparation:\n\nTaste:\n- Generally very sweet\n- Often described as having a sugary, somewhat bland flavor\n- Can taste slightly chalky or powdery\n- Many people find it less appealing in taste compared to buttercream frosting\n\nHow it's made:\n1. Ingredients:\n- Powdered sugar\n- Water\n- Corn syrup or glycerin\n- Gelatin (sometimes)\n\n2. Basic preparation method:\n- Mix powdered sugar with liquid ingredients\n- Knead until smooth and pliable\n- Roll out into a thin sheet\n- Can be colored with food coloring\n- Used to cover cakes or create decorative shapes\n\nThere are two main types:\n1. Rolled fondant (used for covering cakes)\n2. Poured fondant (used for fillings and coating)\n\nWhile fondant creates smooth, professional-looking cake decorations, many people prefer to remove it before eating due to its less appealing taste. It's primarily valued for its aesthetic qualities in cake decorating.\n\nWould you like more details about fondant?",
